## Deploying

See `infrastructure/README.md` for the local Docker Compose flow and the Terraform
skeleton under `infrastructure/terraform/` (defaults to `{{ aws_region }}`).
{%- if has_typescript and ts_agent_framework == "vercel_ai_sdk" %}

**TS agent on Vercel**: with `{{ ts_project_root }}/` set as the project's
Vercel root directory, `{{ ts_source_root }}/index.ts` is already at a path
Vercel auto-detects for Express (`src/index.ts`) — no `vercel.json` needed,
deploy is zero-config
([Vercel's Express docs](https://vercel.com/docs/frameworks/backend/express)).
The existing `app.listen(PORT)` pattern in `index.ts` works as-is on Vercel
(it also supports `export default app` instead, but this template doesn't
need that variant). Set `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` (and any other `TS_AGENT_*`
vars from `.env.example`) in the Vercel project's dashboard — same
variables as local `.env`, different delivery mechanism, not automatically
synced between the two. Streaming (`/agent/chat`) works on Vercel's default
Node.js runtime with no special configuration
([Vercel's streaming docs](https://vercel.com/docs/functions/streaming-functions))
— no Edge runtime needed. If a conversation needs longer than the plan's
default function duration to stream a full response, see
[max duration](https://vercel.com/docs/functions/limitations#max-duration)
for how to raise it via `vercel.json`.
{%- endif %}

## Integrations

**n8n calling this project** (outbound from n8n's perspective): every agent's
`POST /chat`{% if include_rag_agent %} (and `rag_agent`'s `POST /api/v1/retrieval`){% endif %} is plain JSON over
HTTP — callable directly from n8n's HTTP Request node.
{%- if primary_chat_agent in ["adk_agent", "both"] %} `{{ adk_agent_dir }}`'s gateway
already supports an optional `X-API-Key` header (`GATEWAY_API_KEY` env var, a
no-op when unset); the LangGraph FastAPI apps don't have this yet — add the
same pattern before exposing one outside a private network.
{%- else %} None of the FastAPI apps require auth out of the box — add an
API-key check before exposing one outside a private network.
{%- endif %}
{%- if include_n8n_webhook %}

**This project calling n8n back** (inbound webhook, the reverse direction): a
generic `POST /webhooks/n8n` route is mounted on every present agent's FastAPI
app (`{{ source_root }}/integrations/n8n_webhook.py`) — HMAC-SHA256-verified via
an `X-Webhook-Signature` header computed over the raw request body with
`N8N_WEBHOOK_SECRET`. Payload shape: `{"event": "...", "data": {...}}`. Add your
own handlers to `EVENT_HANDLERS` in that file; unrecognized events are accepted
(200) but not dispatched.
{%- endif %}
{%- if include_calendar_integration %}

**Google Calendar** (`{{ source_root }}/integrations/google_calendar.py`):
`GoogleCalendarClient` — list/create events, find open slots. Needs a
pre-obtained OAuth2 refresh token (`GOOGLE_CALENDAR_REFRESH_TOKEN` +
`GOOGLE_CALENDAR_CLIENT_ID`/`_SECRET`) — see the module's docstring for the
one-time consent-flow setup this template deliberately doesn't automate.
{%- endif %}
{%- if include_marketing_integrations %}

**Marketing** (`{{ source_root }}/integrations/{eventbrite,linkedin,canva}.py`):
thin clients for publishing an Eventbrite event, posting a LinkedIn update, and
generating a Canva asset from a brand template — each needs its own API
token/credential (see each module for the exact env var names).
{%- endif %}
{%- if include_meeting_intelligence %}

**Meeting intelligence** (`{{ source_root }}/integrations/meeting_intelligence.py`):
`extract_action_items(transcript)` turns a raw transcript (from a
Granola/Fireflies webhook, or pasted manually) into structured action
items/decisions/owners/deadlines via one LLM call. This module doesn't fetch
transcripts itself — wire your transcript source to call it, e.g. from the
`include_n8n_webhook` receiver's `EVENT_HANDLERS`.
{%- endif %}
{%- if include_ragas_grader %}

**Ragas grader** (`{{ eval_root }}/graders/ragas_grader.py`): an additional
LLM-judge grader (faithfulness/answer-relevancy/context-precision) wired into
`make eval-heuristic` alongside the existing heuristic graders. **Known issue**
(verified 2026-07-14): the current `ragas` release has a broken top-level
import due to an upstream packaging bug — this module catches that and skips
ragas scoring gracefully rather than crashing the eval run, but produces no
real scores until ragas ships a fix. Check `ragas`'s changelog before relying
on this.
{%- endif %}
{%- if include_promptfoo %}

**Promptfoo** (`promptfoo.config.yaml`): a config-driven eval harness, run via
`make promptfoo-eval`{% if include_rag_agent %} (needs `rag_agent` running — `make rag-up` first){% else %} (targets `RAG_AGENT_URL`-style `/chat` on port 8011 — point it
at your custom RAG service){% endif %}.
Hits `/chat` directly over HTTP with its own assertions, alongside (not
instead of) the Python eval suite.
{%- endif %}
{%- if include_composio %}

**Composio** (`{{ source_root }}/integrations/composio.py`):
`get_tools()`/`execute_tool()` — discover and execute third-party app actions
(Gmail, Slack, GitHub, hundreds more) via Composio's unified API. Connect an
account once via Composio's own dashboard/CLI first.
{%- endif %}
{%- if include_web_research %}

**Web research** (`{{ source_root }}/integrations/web_research.py`):
`research(query)` runs GPT-Researcher end-to-end and returns a markdown
report. Needs GPT-Researcher's own LLM + search-provider env vars (e.g.
`OPENAI_API_KEY` + `TAVILY_API_KEY`), not this project's settings. **Known
issue** (verified 2026-07-14): `gpt-researcher`'s `spacy` dependency has no
Python 3.14 wheel yet — pin an older Python (3.12 confirmed working) if
`uv sync` fails.
{%- endif %}
{%- if has_typescript and ts_agent_framework == "vercel_ai_sdk" %}

**TS agent** (`{{ ts_project_root }}/{{ ts_source_root }}/agent/`): a
Vercel AI SDK tool-calling agent (`streamText` + `tool()`, automatic
multi-step tool use), mounted at `POST /agent/chat` on the existing Express
app — no separate service or port. `agent/handler.ts` is a plain
`(req: Request) => Response` function, so it also drops straight into a
Next.js App Router route handler unchanged if this project is (or becomes)
Next.js-based. Reads `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` (same key as the Python agents).
See `.agents/skills/framework-selection/SKILL.md` for when to reach for
this vs. ADK/LangGraph. Answer-only smoke eval (NOT retrieval grading — the
TS agent has no search step, unlike the Python backends): `make ts-dev`
in one terminal, `make ts-agent-eval` in another — scores token overlap
against `data/corpus/golden_qa.jsonl` the same way `citation.py`'s
`grade_answer_overlap` does for the Python backends, writes
`evals/reports/output/heuristic_results_ts_agent.json`.
{%- endif %}
{%- if frontend_backend_topology == "split_service" %}

**split_service** (`{{ ts_project_root }}/` + `{{ source_root }}/middleware/`):
two independently-deployed services sharing identity via Supabase Auth JWT —
FOIA-Fluent's production shape (`dssg/projects/FOIA-Fluent`), not a single
process. `{{ ts_project_root }}/src/middleware.ts` is the Next.js Edge
route gate (session check, redirects unauthenticated requests to `/login`);
`{{ source_root }}/middleware/auth.py`'s `get_current_user_id` FastAPI
dependency verifies the same JWT server-side (HS256 or RS256/JWKS,
auto-detected) and is mounted on every present agent's FastAPI app.
Local dev needs no live Supabase project — `get_current_user_id` returns a
fixed `DEV_USER_ID` whenever `SUPABASE_URL` is unset.

Run both sides locally: `make ts-install && make ts-dev` (frontend, port
3000) and {% if include_rag_agent %}`make rag-up` (backend, port 8011){% else %}`make {{ lgmk }}-up` (backend){% endif %} in separate
terminals. Deploy split: `vercel.json` builds the frontend for Vercel;
`railway.toml` starts the backend under uvicorn for Railway. Fill in
`SUPABASE_URL`/`SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`/`SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET`/`BACKEND_CORS_ORIGINS`
(backend) and `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`/`NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`
(frontend) from a real Supabase project before first deploy — both sides run
without them locally, but auth is a no-op (everyone is `DEV_USER_ID`) until
they're set.
{%- endif %}
